00:00:05.240 --> 00:00:09.640
 done before really comes into play into whether you can get that

00:00:09.640 --> 00:00:14.030
 job later on or not. So you can start your career without any type

00:00:14.030 --> 00:00:18.420
 of training, and the military provides all the training for you. There

00:00:18.420 --> 00:00:22.810
 are other STEM jobs, for instance if you wanna go to NASA, if you

00:00:22.810 --> 00:00:27.210
 want to work at DARPA, like really high level places like that, that

00:00:27.210 --> 00:00:31.600
 you need a degree. You have to have a bachelor's of science something

00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:35.990
 that's accredited by an institution to even be considered for the

00:00:35.990 --> 00:00:40.390
 job at all. So in that case, your training is definitely required.

